latestPosts.caption:
Somewhere between silence and surrender, I met myself.

In the solitude of the mountains, 
in the quiet eyes of animals,
in the wind that didn’t care who I was
I felt... seen.

No words. No roles. No noise.
Just nature... mirroring back parts of me I had long forgotten.

The uniform gave me strength.
But the land it gave me depth.
And slowly, what I believed to be good or bad began to feel like just... another story.

I’m not letting go of who l was.
I’m just reaching gently... towards who l’m becoming.....
